# ShadowCanvas — Developer Documentation

---

## 1. Project Overview

ShadowCanvas is a real-time collaborative digital canvas platform that allows multiple users to draw, annotate, and create together simultaneously. It supports AI-assisted element generation, persistent canvas storage, OAuth-based authentication, and a fully automated CI/CD deployment pipeline.

---

## 2. Tech Stack

Frontend: React, Vite, HTML Canvas API, Socket.io Client
Backend: Node.js, Express, Socket.io, Mongoose
Database: MongoDB Atlas
Authentication: Google OAuth 2.0, GitHub OAuth, JWT
AI: Google Gemini API (gemini-2.5-flash)
Containerization: Docker, Docker Compose
CI/CD: Jenkins (Master-Agent architecture)
Cloud: AWS EC2 (ap-south-1)
Reverse Proxy: Nginx
SSL: Let's Encrypt (Certbot)
Monitoring: Prometheus, Grafana
Security Scanning: Trivy
Registry: Docker Hub

---

## 3. System Architecture

The system follows a microservices-style deployment using Docker Compose with four containers running on the Jenkins Agent EC2 instance:

- frontend — Nginx serving the React build, proxying API and Socket calls to backend
- backend — Node.js Express server handling REST API, Socket.io, and OAuth
- prometheus — Metrics collection
- grafana — Metrics visualization dashboard

The Jenkins Master EC2 instance runs Jenkins only and communicates with the Agent via SSH to trigger builds and deployments.

Flow:
1. Developer pushes code to GitHub
2. GitHub webhook triggers Jenkins pipeline on the master
3. Jenkins master delegates the job to the agent via SSH
4. Agent runs the pipeline: install → test → build Docker images → scan → push to Docker Hub → deploy via Docker Compose

---

## 4. CI/CD Pipeline Stages

Stage 1 — Checkout: Clones the repository from GitHub main branch

Stage 2 — Install Backend Dependencies: Runs npm install in the backend directory

Stage 3 — Run Backend Tests: Runs Jest test suite with environment variables injected

Stage 4 — Lint and Audit Backend: Runs npm audit to check for vulnerabilities

Stage 5 — Build Docker Images: Builds frontend image with VITE_API_URL build arg set to https://shadowcanvas.duckdns.org. Builds backend image.

Stage 6 — Security Scan (Trivy): Scans both Docker images for known CVEs

Stage 7 — Push Images: Logs into Docker Hub and pushes both images (himaneeshj/shadowcanvas-frontend, himaneeshj/shadowcanvas-backend)

Stage 8 — Deploy: Writes backend.env from Jenkins credentials and runs docker compose pull followed by docker compose up -d

Stage 9 — Cleanup: Runs docker system prune -f to free disk space

