## 5. Module Implementation Details

MODULE 1 — User Registration and Session Management
- Google OAuth 2.0 and GitHub OAuth handled via Passport.js strategies
- JWT tokens issued on successful authentication
- Tokens stored client-side and sent in Authorization headers
- Session expiry handled with token validation middleware
- Callback URLs: https://shadowcanvas.duckdns.org/auth/google/callback and https://shadowcanvas.duckdns.org/auth/github/callback

MODULE 2 — Canvas Creation and Basic Drawing
- HTML Canvas API used for rendering
- Mouse and touch events captured for freehand drawing
- Eraser, clear canvas, and brush size controls implemented
- Canvas initialized with default white background on creation

MODULE 3 — Real-Time Collaboration
- Socket.io manages WebSocket connections between users
- Drawing actions broadcast to all users in the same room via room codes
- Disconnection and reconnection handled gracefully
- Active user presence tracked server-side and broadcast to the room

MODULE 4 — Drawing Tools and Interaction
- Tools: freehand pen, shapes (rectangle, circle, diamond, arrow), text, image upload, eraser, select
- Color picker and brush size controls
- Undo/Redo implemented per user using action history stack
- Zoom control (percentage display) for canvas navigation

MODULE 5 — Canvas Storage and Reusability
- Canvas state saved as JSON snapshots to MongoDB via POST /api/canvas/save
- Canvases listed per user via GET /api/canvas
- Canvas loaded by room code via GET /api/canvas/:roomCode
- Canvas deleted via DELETE /api/canvas/:id
- Share functionality via room codes

MODULE 6 — AI-Assisted Canvas and Auto-Save
- Gemini API (gemini-2.5-flash model) integrated via @google/genai package
- AI chat panel accessible from the canvas toolbar
- User sends natural language prompt → backend calls Gemini → response rendered as canvas elements
- GEMINI_API_KEY stored in backend.env
- Auto-save triggers on canvas state changes at defined intervals

