## 6. Environment Variables (backend.env)

PORT — Port the backend server listens on (5000)
MONGO_URI — MongoDB Atlas connection string
JWT_SECRET — Secret key for signing JWT tokens
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID — Google OAuth app client ID
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET — Google OAuth app client secret
GOOGLE_CALLBACK_URL — https://shadowcanvas.duckdns.org/auth/google/callback
GITHUB_CLIENT_ID — GitHub OAuth app client ID
GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET — GitHub OAuth app client secret
GITHUB_CALLBACK_URL — https://shadowcanvas.duckdns.org/auth/github/callback
FRONTEND_URL — https://shadowcanvas.duckdns.org
EMAIL_USER — Gmail address for email notifications
EMAIL_PASS — Gmail app password
GEMINI_API_KEY — Google Gemini API key

---

## 7. Nginx Configuration

Nginx runs inside the frontend container and handles:
- HTTP to HTTPS redirect (port 80 → 443)
- SSL termination using Let's Encrypt certificates mounted from /etc/letsencrypt
- Proxying /api/ requests to http://backend:5000
- Proxying /auth/ requests to http://backend:5000
- Proxying /socket.io/ requests to http://backend:5000 with WebSocket upgrade headers
- Serving the React static build from /usr/share/nginx/html

---

## 8. Docker Compose Services

frontend — Image: himaneeshj/shadowcanvas-frontend. Ports: 80, 443. Volumes: /etc/letsencrypt mounted read-only for SSL certificates.

backend — Image: himaneeshj/shadowcanvas-backend. Port: 5000. Env file: backend.env.

prometheus — Image: prom/prometheus. Port: 9090.

grafana — Image: grafana/grafana. Port: 3000.

---

## 9. Infrastructure

Jenkins Master — EC2 instance running Jenkins on port 8080. Communicates with agent via SSH. Hosts Jenkins credentials store for all secrets.

Jenkins Agent — EC2 instance running Docker, Node.js, Trivy, Certbot. Hosts the application containers. Domain shadowcanvas.duckdns.org points to this instance's public IP via DuckDNS.

SSL Certificate — Issued by Let's Encrypt via Certbot for shadowcanvas.duckdns.org. Stored at /etc/letsencrypt/live/shadowcanvas.duckdns.org/.

---

## 10. Local Setup Guide

1. Clone the repository: git clone https://github.com/Dinesh-1208/shadowCanvas
2. Navigate to backend folder and create a .env file with all variables listed in Section 6
3. Run npm install and npm start in the backend folder
4. Navigate to frontend folder
5. Create a .env file with VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000
6. Run npm install and npm run dev
7. Frontend runs on http://localhost:5173
8. Backend runs on http://localhost:5000

